# The new score-list, resulting from this post: https://github.com/flide/8VIM/discussions/260
# The new score-list is based on the (calculated) writing time and the movement Quality of writing a two-position-combination
#
# Movement-Quality: "0" whenever Forced Stops OR/AND a position of Layer 4 is involved; "1" for the rest of the movements
#
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
#   (For better readability, hereafter all numbers are rounded to 3 digits)
# First the reciprocal of the shortest and the longest writing time is calculated: (1/0.608 = 1.644) and (1/1.592 = 0.628)
# ... resulting in reciprocal values ranging from 1.644 to 0.628
# Next these values are divided by the higher one to get a max. value of 1.0
# ... resulting in a scaled value of 1.0 for the two-position-combination with the shortest writing time
# ... and of 0.382 for the two-position-combination with the longest writing time
#
# This is the range of the scores for all two-position-combination with a Movement-Quality of "1"
#
# Two-position-combination with a Movement-Quality of "0" are further scaled down to reach a maximum of 0.382
# For that the calculated score of such a two-position-combination is multiplied by 0.382
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
#
# Here is how to calculate the score for any two-position-combination
#
# 1. get its Movement-Quality
#
# 2. for Movement-Quality of "1" calculate:
# ... Score = (1 / writing time) / 1.644 = 1.644 / writing time
#
# 3. for Movement-Quality of "0" calculate:
# ... Score = 0,382 x (1 / writing time) / 1.644 = 0.382 x 1.644 / writing time
#
